An representation of the XML 
<code>SignedInfo</code> element as defined in the 
<a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/xmldsig-core/"> W3C Recommendation for XML-Signature Syntax and Processing</a>. The XML Schema Definition is defined as: 
<pre><code>
 &lt;element name="SignedInfo" type="ds:SignedInfoType"/&gt;
 &lt;complexType name="SignedInfoType"&gt;
   &lt;sequence&gt;
     &lt;element ref="ds:CanonicalizationMethod"/&gt;
     &lt;element ref="ds:SignatureMethod"/&gt;
     &lt;element ref="ds:Reference" maxOccurs="unbounded"/&gt;
   &lt;/sequence&gt;
   &lt;attribute name="Id" type="ID" use="optional"/&gt;
 &lt;/complexType&gt;
 </code></pre> A 
<code>SignedInfo</code> instance may be created by invoking one of the 
<a href="XMLSignatureFactory.html#newSignedInfo(javax.xml.crypto.dsig.CanonicalizationMethod,javax.xml.crypto.dsig.SignatureMethod,java.util.List)"><code>newSignedInfo</code></a> methods of the 
<a href="XMLSignatureFactory.html" title="class in javax.xml.crypto.dsig"><code>XMLSignatureFactory</code></a> class.
